1. Introduction
Trevor Drayton respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how I collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use my mobile application Goblin Guide (“App”).

2. Data We Collect
a. Personal Data

Identifiers: email address (if you contact support)

Usage Data: device type, OS version, app usage analytics (via third-party services like Google Analytics)

b. Advertising Data

Advertising identifiers (e.g. Google Advertising ID) used by Google AdMob to serve personalized ads. You may opt out via your device settings.

3. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)
Consent: We process advertising identifiers and analytics only with your consent.

Contractual necessity: If you make an in-app purchase, we process your purchase data to fulfill that transaction.

Legitimate interests: We use aggregated, anonymized analytics to improve the App.

4. How We Use Your Data
To operate and maintain the App

To process in-app purchases and deliver “Remove Ads” feature

To serve personalized ads via Google AdMob

To comply with legal obligations

5. Data Sharing
We share data only with:

Google for AdMob advertising and Google Analytics

Apple/Google for in-app purchase validation

We do not sell your personal data to third parties.

6. Data Retention
We retain personal data only as long as necessary to provide the App and comply with legal obligations. Usage analytics data is retained in aggregated, anonymized form.

7. Your Rights (GDPR)
If you are in the EEA, you have the right to:

Access your personal data

Rectify inaccurate data

Erase your data (“right to be forgotten”)

Restrict or object to processing

Withdraw consent at any time

To exercise these rights, contact us at:
Email: unofficialgoblinguide@gmail.com

8. Cookies and Tracking
Our App uses mobile advertising identifiers and SDK cookies managed by Google AdMob. You can opt out of personalized ads via your device settings (“Limit Ad Tracking” on iOS, “Opt out of Ads Personalization” on Android).

9. Security
We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data.

10. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy in the App and at https://yourdomain.com/privacy-policy.
